## Usage

{% if design.transport == "http" %}
### Start the server

```bash
mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

The server starts on `http://{{ design.http_host }}:{{ design.http_port }}` by default. Override:

```bash
MCP_HOST=0.0.0.0 MCP_PORT=9000 mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

### Expose it for remote MCP clients

Expose the running HTTP server with the provider you prefer. For easy setup, we recommend [`mcp-use`](https://github.com/mcp-use/mcp-use):

```bash
npx @mcp-use/tunnel {{ design.http_port }}
```

Then add the public connector URL from your hosting or tunneling provider in your MCP client.

### Local MCP client config

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ design.server_name | replace('_', '-') }}": {
      "url": "http://localhost:{{ design.http_port }}/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }} .
docker run -p {{ design.http_port }}:{{ design.http_port }} mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```
{% else %}
### Start the server

```bash
mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

### Add to your MCP client

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ design.server_name | replace('_', '-') }}": {
      "command": "mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}",
      "args": []
    }
  }
}
```
{% if design.backend and ((design.backend.backend_type.value == "protocol") and (design.backend.env_vars.get("PROTOCOL") == "http" or design.tools | selectattr("impl.strategy", "equalto", "http_call") | list) or (design.backend.auth and design.backend.auth.auth_type)) %}

The generated `mcp.json` also includes the `env` block for the upstream base URL and auth placeholders.
{% endif %}
